comment:
* Product-specific information about the display or the directly connected device on the
 * display chain. For example, if the display is transitively connected, this field may contain
 * product information about the intermediate device.

variables.name: CONNECTION_TO_SINK_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: The device connection to the display sink is unknown.

variables.name: CONNECTION_TO_SINK_BUILT_IN
variables.comment: The display sink is built-in to the device

variables.name: CONNECTION_TO_SINK_DIRECT
variables.comment: The device is directly connected to the display sink.

variables.name: CONNECTION_TO_SINK_TRANSITIVE
variables.comment: The device is transitively connected to the display sink.

methods.name: public String getManufacturerPnpId()
methods.comment:
* Returns the Manufacturer Plug and Play ID. This ID identifies the manufacture according to
     * the list: https://uefi.org/PNP_ID_List. It consist of 3 characters, each character
     * is an uppercase letter (A-Z).
     * @return Manufacturer Plug and Play ID.

methods.name: public int getModelYear()
methods.comment:
* @return Model year of the device. Return -1 if not available. Typically,
     * one of model year or manufacture year is available.

methods.name: public int getManufactureYear()
methods.comment:
* @return The year of manufacture, or -1 it is not available. Typically,
     * one of model year or manufacture year is available.

methods.name: public int getManufactureWeek()
methods.comment:
* @return The week of manufacture which ranges from 1 to 53, or -1 it is not available.
     * Typically, it is not present if model year is available.

methods.name: public ManufactureDate getManufactureDate()
methods.comment:
* @return Manufacture date. Typically exactly one of model year or manufacture
     * date will be present.
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public int getConnectionToSinkType()
methods.comment:
* @return How the current device is connected to the display sink. For example, the display
     * can be connected immediately to the device or there can be a receiver in between.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
